  "body": "This is a non-comprehensive list of changes we want to introduce in the v3.0, the upcoming major release. We will use this opportunity to introduce some breaking changes by removing contracts we don't see much demand for (such as Crowdsales), and improving others we could can be done better (like Roles and Access Control in general).\r\n\r\nFor more information about the v3.0 release, head to [our roadmap](#2068).\r\n\r\n - [x] Migrate to Solidity v0.6.x [#2080]\r\n - [x] Design a new access control solution (see the discussion in [this forum post](https://forum.openzeppelin.com/t/redesigning-accesscontrol-for-the-openzeppelin-contracts/2177))\r\n - [x] Include optional extensions to some of our standard implementations (such as `ERC20Detailed`, possibly `ERC721Metadata` and `ERC721Enumerable`)\r\n - [x] Review contracts in `drafts` and either remove or promote out of there\r\n - [x] Make IERC721 `contract`s `interface`s instead (see [here](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/pull/2080#discussion_r377276127))\r\n - [x] Remove contracts or libraries made obsolete by v0.6, such as `Address.toPayable()` (https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/issues/2118)\r\n - [x] Review naming conventions, including usage of leading underscores in `internal` functions in contracts but not in libraries\r\n - [x] Consider marking some contracts that should only be used via inheritance `abstract` (such as `Ownable` and `ERC20`)\r\n - [x] Close all issues on the [v3.0 milestone](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/milestone/8)\r\n - [x] Perform some [directory and naming cleanup](https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/openzeppelin-contracts/issues/2060)\r\n - [x] Fix documentation website build (requires fixing https://github.com/OpenZeppelin/solidity-docgen/issues/133)\r\n - [x] Review naming of libraries: singular vs plural, `Strings`, `Counters`, `EnumerableSet`...\r\n - [x] Review malleability protections in `ECDSA.recover`",
